You'll have to make the collapsing on the client side if you want to use the scroll. You could for instance do a query like:
````
GET _search?scroll=1m
{
  "query": {
    "exists": {
        "field": "session"
    }
  },
  "sort": [
     {
        "session": {
           "order": "desc"
        },
        "timestamp": {
            "order": "asc"
        }
     }
  ]
}
````
... and then for each result set you would keep the first result of each session id.
We're also iterating on a collapse feature for search requests but only pagination would be possible (no scroll):
https://github.com/elastic/elasticsearch/pull/22337

